to the editor how good of congress to pass a rosie the riveter bill that authorizes a memorial park honoring the millions of women who worked in the defense industry during world war ii news article oct 22 their pluck not only changed the course of the war but also dramatically changed the course of feminism in america as you report the rosie the riveter depicted in the original posters was a fictitious character but a real rosie was soon discovered her name was rose will monroe and she was a riveter at the willow run aircraft factory in ypsilanti mich ms monroe was recruited for a film urging people to buy war bonds her story was part of a recent exhibition that i curated at the new york historical society ms monroe should also be remembered by those creating the rosie the riveter ww2 home front national historic park ann weissmann new york oct 23 2000

